5:
There's no point struggling! Just turn
yourselves in already!
21:
That was so easy, it was kinda sad.
Did they really need all three of us
for this?
31: It feels like someone's watching us...
37:
Oh, is that all? It was probably a
journalist for a magazine or
something.
44:
Yep, they probably wanted to write
about how the super strong,
capable Guild Knights stopped the
wild attackers from that strange
new city.
48:
So this was all planned from the
start?
51:
It's more like... They were waiting for
this chance, since those loose
cannons from your city were gonna
strike anyway.
59:
Anything that boosts the Guild
Knights' reputation is a win in my
book. Gives us more staying power,
at least.
62:
Guess the cat's outta the bag
though. Had to happen eventually.
67:
He asked for you, despite knowing
this would happen.
72:
You figured it out beforehand?
Wow... Well, not like I was trying to
hide it.
77:
Is that why you asked us to stay in
our school uniforms?
80:
When I first started helping the Guild
Knights, I heard that not everyone
had to wear the uniform.
82:
But then you also explicitly said it's
better if we stay in our own clothes.
86:
Can't hurt to show that we've got a
good working relationship with you
and yours, right?
89:
Besides, at the end of the day, we've
got our own problems, and you've
got yours. We shouldn't be grouped
together all the time.
94:
Huh. I totally thought you were just a
weirdo into school uniforms.
104: I wonder if that was a warning...
111:
Whenever Zekhel gets like that, it's
usually to give us a heads-up.
116:
Why wouldn't he just tell it to us
straight?
120: You gotta ask him that, not me...
125:
Is he worried about other people
taking advantage of us?
129:
Hmm... Probably? He's definitely
worried about us having the
freedom to make our own decisions,
that's for sure.
133:
With what happened with the Vesta
before, he must be worried about
what his superiors might do.
136:
...The Guild is watching over the
people from Shibuya who are still
asleep, correct?
139:
In a worst case scenario, there's a
possibility they could be used as
hostages...
142:
Zekhel and that other Guild
personthey wanted you to
represent Shibuya, right, Ayumu?
152:
It's a bad idea. You're not cut out for
that kinda stuff.
157:
Yeah... I was going to ask them for
help, but...
161:
Honestly? It's best if someone from
Shibuya takes charge of their own
town.
166:
In that case, I know the perfect
candidate.
176: This is... a lot of responsibility...
179: I've only been a teacher up until now
187:
I remember exactly how serious you
were back then.
201:
I'm not the most capable person,
but if you're truly fine with that, then
I'll do it.
205: You're more capable than you think.
211:
*sigh* I'm more of an emotional
person than I thought.
215:
Well, that's enough standing around.
Time to get to work.
220:
I wonder what my middle school self
would say if I told her everything
that's happened?
223:
The two most cowardly people she
knew have changed for the better.
226: She wouldn't believe me at first...
229:
But that's fine. I'd just prove it to her
instead.
